US authorities said Monday they were liquidating Bernard L. Madoff Investment Securities LLC of New York, following his arrest for alleged fraud to the tune of 50 billion dollars.
Fortis Bank Netherlands said Monday it stood to lose up to a billion euros in the suspected fraud scam run by New York trader Bernard Madoff.
British bank HSBC, the world's third-biggest bank by market capitalisation, said on Monday it had exposure of about 1.0 billion dollars to suspected fraud by US financier Bernard Madoff.
French investment bank Natixis said Monday it may be an indirect victim of Wall Street money manager Bernard Madoff with exposure of up to euro450 million ($600.3 million).
